                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 33.035,
                                "byte_start": 28672,
                                "byte_stop": 160852,
                                "text": "Number 483 and 484, Lawrence Speiser against Randall, and Prince against the City and County of San Francisco."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 33.035,
                        "stop": 170.053,
                        "byte_start": 160852,
                        "byte_stop": 708901,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 16091,
                            "name": "Mr. Attorney General",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/attorney_general",
                            "last_name": "General",
                            "roles": null,
                            "thumbnail": null,
                            "length_of_service": 0,
                            "identifier": "attorney_general"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 33.035,
                                "stop": 45.067,
                                "byte_start": 160852,
                                "byte_stop": 209021,
                                "text": "These cases involved the same constitutional provision, Article 20, Section 19 of the California Constitution and Revenue and Taxation Code Section 32."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 45.067,
                                "stop": 61.761,
                                "byte_start": 209021,
                                "byte_stop": 275790,
                                "text": "The issues in these cases are exactly the same as the preceding cases with the exception that it does not involve a question of freedom of religion or establishment of religion nor is there an organizational question involved."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 61.761,
                                "stop": 64.933,
                                "byte_start": 275790,
                                "byte_stop": 288434,
                                "text": "We are dealing with a privilege."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 64.933,
                                "stop": 66.967,
                                "byte_start": 288434,
                                "byte_stop": 296584,
                                "text": "There is no question about that."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 66.967,
                                "stop": 82.635,
                                "byte_start": 296584,
                                "byte_stop": 359278,
                                "text": "We aren\u0027t saying that there is a right to an exemption and even historically, we will not find the same granting of exemption for veterans in this area as it has been granted to churches."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 82.635,
                                "stop": 94.011,
                                "byte_start": 359278,
                                "byte_stop": 404731,
                                "text": "I like to suggest that there\u0027s a classification -- distinction that should be made between exemptions, hence, they are given and when you take an exemption away."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 94.011,
                                "stop": 104.226,
                                "byte_start": 404731,
                                "byte_stop": 445586,
                                "text": "For example, it will not be proper, it would seem to me, to grant an exemption of any kind to redheads, Republicans or adulterers."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 104.226,
                                "stop": 122.303,
                                "byte_start": 445586,
                                "byte_stop": 517893,
                                "text": "But if you grant exemptions to the general public, it may be bad and it would be bad to take away exemptions or to exclude from exemptions in general, redheads, churches with red-headed ministers or Republicans or adulterers."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 122.303,
                                "stop": 131.112,
                                "byte_start": 517893,
                                "byte_stop": 553211,
                                "text": "Now, I am basing my argument on a broader scale than the preceding counsel."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 131.112,
                                "stop": 136.958,
                                "byte_start": 553211,
                                "byte_stop": 576512,
                                "text": "I contend that we do have an issue, the constitutional amendment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 136.958,
                                "stop": 139.673,
                                "byte_start": 576512,
                                "byte_stop": 587379,
                                "text": "We have it in issue for several reasons."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 139.673,
                                "stop": 152.652,
                                "byte_start": 587379,
                                "byte_stop": 639310,
                                "text": "We have it in issue because the State Supreme Court construed it, interpret it and in its findings on free speech question, it was talking about the constitutional amendment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 152.652,
                                "stop": 156.961,
                                "byte_start": 639310,
                                "byte_stop": 656551,
                                "text": "We have it in issue because the State Supreme Court said it was self-executing."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 156.961,
                                "stop": 157.88,
                                "byte_start": 656551,
                                "byte_stop": 660208,
                                "text": "It was mandatory."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 157.88,
                                "stop": 159.295,
                                "byte_start": 660208,
                                "byte_stop": 665955,
                                "text": "It was prohibitory."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 159.295,
                                "stop": 162.299,
                                "byte_start": 665955,
                                "byte_stop": 677972,
                                "text": "It applied to all exemptions in the State."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 162.299,
                                "stop": 170.053,
                                "byte_start": 677972,
                                "byte_stop": 708901,
                                "text": "And it -- and it said that Revenue and Taxation Code Section 32 was merely a procedural device."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
